# Optional: the host IP printed in `make pg.endpoint` / `make pg.ip` and used
# in the .pgpass line. The ports are published on ALL host interfaces
# (listen 0.0.0.0), so any host address reaches them; this just controls which
# one is reported. Default: the source IP of the primary default route.
# PG_HOST_IP=

# Optional: override the host-side ports if 5432/5433/5434 already collide with
# something on the host. Defaults shown.
# PG_ACTIVE_PORT=5432
# PG_STAGING_PORT=5433
# PG_DIRECT_PORT=5434

# Optional: pin the pg-bouncer container's static IP.
#
# Default (when this is unset): the script reads
#   incus network get incusbr0 ipv4.address
# and uses .10 inside whatever subnet incusbr0 happens to be on. So with
# a 192.168.100.0/24 bridge you get 192.168.100.10; with a 10.224.165.0/24
# bridge you get 10.224.165.10; etc.
#
# Override here only if you need a specific address (e.g. you already have
# something on .10 in that subnet).
# PG_BOUNCER_IP=
